data.name: Argument
data.value: Cannot process argument because the value of argument "{0}" is not valid. Change the value of the "{0}" argument and run the operation again.

data.name: InvalidScopeIdArgument
data.value: Cannot process argument because the value of parameter "{0}" is not valid. Valid values are "Global", "Local", or "Script", or a number relative to the current scope (0 through the number of scopes where 0 is the current scope and 1 is its parent). Change the value of the "{0}" parameter and run the operation again.

data.name: ArgumentNull
data.value: Cannot process argument because the value of argument "{0}" is null. Change the value of argument "{0}" to a non-null value.

data.name: ArgumentOutOfRange
data.value: Cannot process argument because the value of argument "{0}" is out of range. Change argument "{0}" to a value that is within range.

data.name: InvalidOperation
data.value: Cannot perform operation because operation "{0}" is not valid. Remove operation "{0}", or investigate why it is not valid.

data.name: NotImplemented
data.value: Cannot perform operation because operation "{0}" is not implemented.

data.name: NotSupported
data.value: Cannot perform operation because operation "{0}" is not supported.

data.name: ObjectDisposed
data.value: Cannot perform operation because object "{0}" has already been disposed.

data.name: ScriptBlockInvokeOnOneClauseOnly
data.value: The script block cannot be invoked because it contains more than one clause. The Invoke() method can only be used on script blocks that contain a single clause.

data.name: CanConvertOneClauseOnly
data.value: The script block cannot be converted because it contains more than one clause. Expressions or control structures are not permitted. Verify that the script block contains exactly one pipeline or command.

data.name: CantConvertEmptyPipeline
data.value: An empty script block cannot be converted. Verify that the script block contains exactly one pipeline or command.

data.name: CanOnlyConvertOnePipeline
data.value: Only a script block that contains exactly one pipeline or command can be converted. Expressions or control structures are not permitted. Verify that the script block contains exactly one pipeline or command.

data.name: CantConvertScriptBlockWithTrap
data.value: A script block that contains a top-level trap statement cannot be converted.

data.name: CantConvertWithUndeclaredVariables
data.value: Cannot generate a PowerShell object for a ScriptBlock dereferencing variables undeclared in the param(...) block. Name of undeclared variable: {0}.

data.name: CantConvertWithNonConstantExpression
data.value: Cannot generate a PowerShell object for a ScriptBlock evaluating non-constant expressions. Non-constant expression: {0}.

data.name: CantConvertWithDynamicExpression
data.value: Cannot generate a PowerShell object for a ScriptBlock evaluating dynamic expressions. Dynamic expression: {0}.

data.name: CantConvertWithScriptBlocks
data.value: Cannot generate a PowerShell object for a ScriptBlock that tries to pass other script blocks inside argument values.

data.name: CantConvertWithCommandInvocations
data.value: Cannot generate a PowerShell object for a ScriptBlock which invokes pipelines, commands or functions to evaluate arguments of the main pipeline.

data.name: CantConvertWithDotSourcing
data.value: Cannot generate a PowerShell object for a ScriptBlock that uses dot sourcing.

data.name: CantConvertWithScriptBlockInvocation
data.value: Cannot generate a PowerShell object for a ScriptBlock that invokes other script blocks.

data.name: CanConvertOneOutputErrorRedir
data.value: The script block cannot be converted to a PowerShell object because it contains forbidden redirection operators.

data.name: CantConvertScriptBlockWithNoContext
data.value: Cannot generate a PowerShell object for a ScriptBlock that does not have an associated operation context.

data.name: HaltCommandException
data.value: The command was stopped by the user.

data.name: DynamicParametersWrongType
data.value: Object "{0}" is the wrong type to return from the dynamicparam block. The dynamicparam block must return either $null, or an object with type [System.Management.Automation.RuntimeDefinedParameterDictionary].

data.name: CantConvertScriptBlockToOpenGenericType
data.value: The script block cannot be converted to an open generic type. Define an appropriate closed generic type, and then retry.

data.name: CantConvertPipelineStartsWithExpression
data.value: Cannot generate a PowerShell object for a ScriptBlock that starts a pipeline with an expression.

data.name: UsingVariableIsUndefined
data.value: The value of the using variable '$using:{0}' cannot be retrieved because it has not been set in the local session.

data.name: CantGetUsingExpressionValueWithSpecifiedVariableDictionary
data.value: Cannot get the value of the Using expression '{0}' in the specified variable dictionary. When creating a PowerShell instance from a script block, the Using expression cannot contain an indexing operation or member-accessing operation.

data.name: WDACCompiledScriptBlockLogTitle
data.value: Compiled Script Block Dot Source

data.name: WDACCompiledScriptBlockLogMessage
data.value: Script block '{0}' invocation into current scope will be disallowed when policy is enforced. Script language mode: {1}, Context language mode: {2}.
